      • getCertificate

        public static java.lang.String getCertificate(java.lang.String certificateParameterValue)
        Checks whether the certificate parameter value is an existing filename. If it is, then the certificate parameter value is returned without any change. If it is not, then it is assumed the certificate parameter value is a certificate itself and the "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----" and "-----END CERTIFICATE-----" strings will be prepended and appended respectively.
        Parameters:
        certificateParameterValue - the "--verify-cert-bundle" CLI input parameter value
        Returns:
        the received string value if such string is an existing filename. the received string with prepended "BEGIN CERTIFICATE" and appended "END CERTIFICATE" strings otherwise.
